1466:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c **** /**
1467:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @brief  Stop DMA-based multimode ADC conversion, disable ADC DMA transfer, disable ADC peripher
1468:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         conversion is on-going.
1469:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @note   Multimode is kept enabled after this function. Multimode DMA bits
1470:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         (MDMA and DMACFG bits of common CCR register) are maintained. To disable
1471:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         multimode (set with HAL_ADCEx_MultiModeConfigChannel()), ADC must be
1472:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         reinitialized using HAL_ADC_Init() or HAL_ADC_DeInit(), or the user can
1473:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         resort to HAL_ADCEx_DisableMultiMode() API.
1474:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @note   In case of DMA configured in circular mode, function
1475:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         HAL_ADCEx_RegularStop_DMA() must be called after this function with handle of
1476:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   *         ADC slave, to properly disable the DMA channel.
1477:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @param hadc ADC handle of ADC master (handle of ADC slave must not be used)
1478:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   * @retval HAL status
1479:Drivers/STM32G4xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32g4xx_hal_adc_ex.c ****   */
